The paper deals with algorithms for the min-cut problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of graph algorithms. The paper presents algorithms for this problem in various settings, including sequential, cut query, and streaming. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
